.TH "init_hash_hw" 9 "init_hash_hw" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
init_hash_hw \- Initialise the hash hardware for a new calculation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" init_hash_hw
.BI "(struct hash_device_data *device_data "  ","
.BI "struct hash_ctx *ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device_data" 12
Structure for the hash device.
.IP "ctx" 12
The hash context.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will enable the bits needed to clear and start a new
calculation.
